Colonies with determinate growth, plate-shaped, composed of flat branches up to a second degree of ramification, sometimes anastomosed, large appressed tubular to tubular corallites arranged mainly laterally on the branches. Coenosteum of dense elaborated spinules throughout (
Wallace & Wolstenholme, 1998
; 
Wallace, 1999
).

